CAPE TOWN - Police in Cape Town have made a breakthrough and arrested a 32-year-old suspect in connection with the murder of a police constable in Khayelitsha earlier in April. In a statement on Friday, Western Cape police spokesperson Novela Potelwa said an investigating team comprising Khayelitsha detectives and Directorate for Priority Crime Investigation (Hawks) members arrested the man on Thursday in connection with the murder of Constable Ncedo Katoyi two weeks ago. READ: One dead, 'officer' injured in Joburg shooting "The team is still in pursuit of more suspects. The 32-year-old will appear in court on Monday in Khayelitsha on a murder charge." Katoyi (39) and his partner had responded to a complaint in Site C where they came under fire from six unknown suspects who also took his service pistol. Katoyi died on the scene. African News Agency